Czech Republic Ambassador Pavel &#344;ez&aacute;&#269; and his wife Nad'a &#344;ez&aacute;&#269;ov&aacute; on Friday invited guests to a late afternoon reception at their residence in Muthaiga.The get-together was in celebration of the National Day of the Czech Republic, which commemorates the date in 1918 when Czechoslovakia was created.In attendance were members of the diplomatic corps, residents in the country, family and friends.